04 April - Corn Bread 

- 1 1/2 cup cornmeal 
- 1/2   cup flour
- 1     cup milk
- 4     teaspoon baking powder
- 1/2   teaspoon salt
- 1     egg beaten 
- 1/4   cup melted fat or oil


Mix conrmeal, flour, salt and baking powder. Mix together milk and egg and add fat. Add milk mixture to cornmeal misture. Stir only enough to mix. Fill greased loaf pan half full. Bake at 425F preheated oven about 25 minutes or until lightly brown. 

Note - if desired add 1/4 cup sugar. May also be used for corn muffins. Corn muffin baking time will be 15-20 minutes. 